Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.base

Class SequenceQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.QueryAdaptor
      • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.QueryList
        • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.base.SequenceQuery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Queryable
    public class SequenceQuery
extends QueryList

    Chains a sequence of queries, i.e. the result() of each query serves as an input into submit(...) of the next query.

    Type of input to submit()
    any class;
    Type of result
    type of the result of the last query in the sequence (if everything went ok - null otherwise)
    Fails if
    any of the queries of the sequence fails
    Author:
    Shayne Flint - 28/3/2012, Ian Davies - 23 Feb. 2021
    See Also:
    CoreQueries

      • get

        public static java.lang.Object get​(java.lang.Object input,
                                   Queryable... queries)

        Get the result of a sequence of queries applied on an object.

        This method is specially designed to work in interaction with CoreQueries static methods to query particular elements of a Graph. Examples:

        return all the OUT edges of a node labelled 'blue': 

         get(node, edges(Direction.OUT), edgeListEndNodes(), selectZeroOrMany(hasTheLabel("blue")));

        return all the children of a (tree)node that have property color='red' 

         get(node, children(), selectZeroOrMany(hasProperty("color", "red")));
        Parameters:
        input - the object on which to apply queries
        queries - the sequence a queries to apply to the object
        Returns:
        the result of the last query
